    "Liberia will formulate a capacity-building strategy for adaptation including awareness/public mobilization, training professionals and vulnerable groups, and strengthening institutions and research for adaptation knowledge dissemination.": 0,
    "Liberia will deploy a NAP monitoring and evaluation (M&E) system integrating adaptation into monitoring systems and including adaptation actions of government and sectors.": 0,
    "Liberia will draft and initiate adaptation strategies by forming an inter-governmental working group and supporting formulation and preparation of an adaptation strategy with methodologies, inputs, and training.": 0,
    "Liberia will develop and deploy sectoral climate risk and vulnerability assessments, including sector-specific monitoring methodologies and improved modeling/estimation methods for climate change risk.": 0,
    "Liberia will establish a climate intelligence center at the EPA, including support systems for spatial/integrated analysis and an agriculture communication and early-warning component.": 0,
    "Liberia will implement proposed adaptation strategies through sectoral strategies under the NAP Process for priority sectors (agriculture, coastal zones, forestry, energy, waste management, fisheries) and cross-cutting sectors (water resources, biodiversity).": 0,
    "Agriculture adaptation strategy: strengthen Ministry of Agriculture capacity; improve integrated pest/disease/weed management and resistant varieties; assess crop vulnerability/suitability by agro-ecological zones; and enhance climate-proof agro-infrastructure to raise farmer productivity.": 0,
    "Agriculture adaptation strategy: support communities via indigenous knowledge dissemination, insurance schemes, early warning/early action systems, vaccination campaigns and disease control to cope with climate variability.": 0,
    "Agriculture adaptation strategy: develop and introduce integrated soil fertility management, water harvesting, and conservation techniques to improve soil fertility and cope with aridity, waterlogging and floods.": 0,
