    "Fisheries adaptation strategy: strengthen capacity of fisheries authorities for research/monitoring/enforcement; support artisanal fishing communities with training, gear and alternative livelihoods; establish monitoring/reporting/verification and adaptive management; support research on climate pressures; identify/map/protect valuable fisheries areas including marine protected areas; reduce external stressors via regulatory measures; integrate fisheries into national adaptation and food security policies; establish early warning and information/communication networks; and regulate fishing to prevent overexploitation.": 0,
    "Forestry adaptation strategy: strengthen FDA capacity and logistics; implement sustainable/alternative livelihoods for forest-dependent communities; promote community forest activities beyond timber extraction; establish comprehensive forest (including NTFPs) monitoring; implement reforestation/afforestation in degraded areas; map and manage forest water catchments; consolidate protected area networks with landscape connectivity; strengthen coordination with other agencies; enforce anti-poaching regulations and a wildlife code of ethics; and implement communication strategies to raise awareness on climate impacts and adaptation.": 0,
